      "text": "Manual 23\nTransmission Expansion and\nInterconnection Manual\nIssued: February 2025\nNote: On May 1, 2024, the NYISO filed with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (the \n“Commission”) in its Docket No. ER24-1915 extensive revisions to its interconnection \nprocedures in response to the Commission’s Order No. 2023. The revisions establish new \nStandard Interconnection Procedures in Attachment HH of the NYISO OATT that replace the \nNYISO’s Standard Large Facility Interconnection Procedures and Small Generator \nInterconnection Procedures set forth in Attachments S, X, and Z to the NYISO OATT. As \nindicated in its filing, the NYISO is implementing the new Standard Interconnection Procedures \nsubject to any determination or modification by the Commission.\nThe interconnection process requirements in this Section 3 of the TEI Manual and the related \nattachments to this manual do not apply for projects participating in the new Standard \nInterconnection Procedures. These requirements only continue to apply for the following \nlimited purposes: (i) the requirements in this Section 3 continue to apply, as applicable, to \nongoing projects that are completing their Class Year Study for Class Year 2023 or Small \nGenerator facilities study pursuant to the transition rules in the Standard Interconnection \nProcedures, and (ii) the requirements in Section 3.5 continue to apply for Load projects seeking \nto interconnect.\nThe NYISO is currently revising the TEI Manual to incorporate the new requirements for its \nStandard Interconnection Procedures as set forth in Attachment HH and in the Technical \nBulletins related to requirements of Attachment HH. In the coming months, NYISO will share its \nproposed TEI Manual revisions with Market Participants at TPAS for Market Participants’ input \nand approval. Market Participants can refer to the Technical Bulletins at NYISO’s Manuals, \nTechnical Bulletins and Guides webpage.\n \nTransmission Expansion and Interconnection Manual | ii\nVersion: 4.3\nEffective Date: 02/07/2025\nCommittee Acceptance: 12/14/2022 BIC\n 12/15/2022 OC\nPrepared By: NYISO Interconnection Projects\nNew York Independent System Operator\n10 Krey Boulevard\nRensselaer, NY 12144\n(518) 356-6060\nwww.nyiso.com\nDisclaimer: The information contained within this manual, along with other NYISO manuals, is intended to be used for \ninformation purposes only, and is subject to change. The NYISO is not responsible for the user’s reliance on these \npublications, or for any erroneous or misleading material.\n©Copyright 1999-2025 New York Independent System Operator\n \nTransmission Expansion and Interconnection Manual | iii\nTable of Contents\nTABLE OF FIGURES.............................................................................................................................................................. V\nREVISION HISTORY ............................................................................................................................................................ VI\n1. INTRODUCTION ............................................................................................................................................................1\n1.1. Transmission Expansion and Interconnection Process Background ............................................. 1\n1.2. NYISO Interconnection Projects Community Portal ......................................................................... 2\n2. TRANSMISSION EXPANSION PROCESS ..........................................................................................................................4\n2.1. Introduction........................................................................................................................................ 4\n2.2. What is a Transmission Expansion?................................................................................................. 4\n2.3. Transmission Interconnection Procedures (TIP).............................................................................. 5\n2.3.1. Basic Information about the TIP ........................................................................................................5\n2.3.2. Getting Started - Transmission Interconnection Application .............................................................7\n2.3.3. Basic Steps of the TIP .........................................................................................................................7\n2.4. Procedures Applicable to Transmission Owner Proposed Upgrades and Expansions That Are \nNot Subject to the TIP......................................................................................................................16\n2.4.1. Introduction .....................................................................................................................................16\n2.4.2. System Impact Study (SIS)................................................................................................................16\n2.4.3. Facilities Study .................................................................................................................................21\n2.4.4. Construction.....................................................................................................................................22\n2.5. Transmission Service Study Procedures........................................................................................22\n2.5.1. Introduction .....................................................................................................................................22\n2.5.2. Getting Started – Transmission Service Study Request....................................................................23\n2.5.3. Transmission Service Study Procedures ...........................................................................................23\n2.5.4. Moving Forward After Completion of the Transmission Service Study ............................................26\n2.6. Award of Incremental TCCs .............................................................................................................26\n3. INTERCONNECTION PROCESS......................................................................................................................................27\n3.1. Introduction......................................................................................................................................27\n3.2. What is an Interconnection? ...........................................................................................................28\n3.3. Large Facility Interconnection Procedures (LFIP) ..........................................................................28\n3.3.1. Basic Information about the LFIP.....................................................................................................28\n3.3.2. Large Facility Interconnection Request............................................................................................32\n3.3.3. Basic Steps of the LFIP......................................................................................................................33\n3.3.4. Materiality Determinations .............................................................................................................53\n3.4. Small Generator Interconnection Procedures (SGIP)....................................................................59\n3.4.1. Basic Information about the SGIP ....................................................................................................59\n3.4.2. Small Generator Interconnection Request.......................................................................................61\n3.4.3. Basic Steps of the SGIP.....................................................................................................................62\n3.4.4. Small Generator Interconnection Studies ........................................................................................62\n3.4.5. Small Generator Intercon",
      "highlights": [
        "Manual 23\nTransmission Expansion and\nInterconnection Manual\nIssued: February 2025\n[...]\nNote: On May 1, 2024, the NYISO filed with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (the \n“Commission”) in its Docket No. ER24-1915 extensive revisions to its interconnection \nprocedures in response to the Commission’s Order No. 2023. The revisions establish new \nStandard Interconnection Procedures in Attachment HH of the NYISO OATT that replace the \nNYISO’s Standard Large Facility Interconnection Procedures and Small Generator \nInterconnection Procedures set forth in Attachments S, X, and Z to the NYISO OATT. As \nindicated in its filing, the NYISO is implementing the new Standard Interconnection Procedures \nsubject to any determination or modification by the Commission.\n[...]\nTransmission Expansion and Interconnection Manual\n[...]\n3. INTERCONNECTION PROCESS......................................................................................................................................27\n[...]\n3.3. Large Facility Interconnection Procedures (LFIP) ..........................................................................28\n[...]\n3.3.1. Basic Information about the LFIP.....................................................................................................28\n[...]\n3.3.2. Large Facility Interconnection Request............................................................................................32\n[...]\n3.3.3. Basic Steps of the LFIP......................................................................................................................33\n[...]\n3.3.4. Materiality Determinations .............................................................................................................53\n[...]\n3.4. Small Generator Interconnection Procedures (SGIP)....................................................................59\n[...]\n.4.2. Small Generator Interconnection Request................................\n[...]\n.......61"
